==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trephine
<hw>Tre*phine"</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A dim. of 1st
<ets>trepan</ets>: cf. F. <ets>tr⟦eacute⟧phine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>An instrument for trepanning, being an
improvement on the trepan. It is a circular or cylindrical saw, with a
handle like that of a gimlet, and a little sharp perforator called the
<xex>center pin</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trephine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trephine
<hw>Tre*phine"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Trephined</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Trephining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To perforate with a trephine;
to trepan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trepid</ent>⟦br⟧
